//Program to print hello world in java.

public class FirstProgram{
  public static void main(Strin[] args){
    System.out.println("Hello World");
  }
}

//Now, the first code is the toughest as it has got so many keywords within it. Don't worry, its not as tough as it seems.

// public - Used to declare that a class or method is accessible to all other classes.
// class - Defines a class named FirstProgram.
// static - Indicates that the main method belongs to the class itself rather than to instances of the class.
// void - Means that the method does not produce any result or output.
// main - It serves as the entry point, The Java Virtual Machine (JVM) looks for the main method to start the execution of the program.
// String[] - It denotes an array of String objects.
// args - It is a parameter of the main method that allows command-line arguments to be passed to the program.
// System.out.println("Hello World") - Prints "Hello World" followed by a new line to the console.
